New Records: Damian Lillard scored 34 points and recorded 7 assists, Giannis Antetokounmpo had a double-double with 31 points, 16 rebounds, and 7 assists, and the Milwaukee Bucks ended a six-game losing streak
Key Match Events: Damian Lillard converted a layup and a three-pointer to give the Bucks a 75-71 lead, Keyonte George went 1-for-2 at the free-throw line, and the Bucks went on a 12-point run to build a 87-72 advantage
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Utah Jazz made 14 three-pointers in the first 24 minutes, and the Milwaukee Bucks dominated the fourth quarter with a commanding lead
